    • Class it.polimi.ingsw.server.model.board.rooms.Square extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • adjacent

          java.util.Map<Direction,​Square> adjacent
          A map that links this to its adjacent square (or null if the connection is "ENDMAP") in every direction.

        • connection

          java.util.Map<Direction,​Connection> connection
          A map that, for every directions, says which kind of connection this square has.

        • map

          java.util.Map<java.lang.Boolean,​java.util.HashMap<Square,​java.lang.Integer>> map
          A "memory" of the distance of any other square in the map (built dynamically). The key of the outer map is a Boolean corresponding to the "throughWalls" property. The inner map saves for each square its distance from this square.

        • players

          java.util.List<Player> players
          The list of players that are currently in this square.

        • room

          Room room
          A reference to the room in which the square is.

        • spawn

          boolean spawn
          A boolean that says if this is a square in which the players can spawn either in the first turn or after death.

        • squareId

          int squareId
          An integer to identify a specific square in its room.

        • tools

          java.util.List<Card> tools
          The list of what's in the square. If the "spawn" boolean is true this is (dynamically) a list of WeaponCard, otherwise it is a list (with a single) AmmoTile.

        • used

          A boolean that says if this effect has been used or is available.

    • Class it.polimi.ingsw.server.model.cards.effects.EffectHandler extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • active

          java.util.List<Target> active
          Every player target goes in this list after being damaged (or marked). It gives us the possibility to have a "memory" of the previous target.

        • activePlayer

          Player activePlayer
          The player who is currently active: the one who has the turn.

        • activeSquare

          Square activeSquare
          The square in which is the activePlayer.

        • inactive

          java.util.List<Target> inactive
          Every player target of the active list goes in this list after being damaged (or marked). It gives us the possibility to have a "memory" of the target damaged twice within the same card.

        • target

          EffectArgument target
          The Target is incapsulated in this more complex class to hold every information needed by the EffectHandler.
